Heat oven to 375 degrees F. Cook broccoli as directed on bag 4 minutes. Place broccoli and turkey in ungreased 9-inch square pan. In 2-quart saucepan, heat cooking sauce and garlic salt to boiling, stirring occasionally. Remove from heat, stir in cheese until melted and smooth. Pour cooking sauce mixture over turkey. Sprinkle with bread crumbs and almonds. Bake uncovered 20 to 25 minutes or until hot and bubbly.